Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and low total CO₂, suggesting possible renal dysfunction and impaired glucose handling. HbA1c is low, indicating no chronic hyperglycemia. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may indicate underlying renal or hepatic pathology. Further nephrological and metabolic evaluation is recommended.
